BRARY EDUCATION IN ISRAEL.DESCRIBES THE HISTORY OF LIBRARY EDUCATION IN ISRAEL, AS OBSERVED AND RECORDEDBY ONE WHO HAS BEEN ACTIVE IN PART OF ITS DEVELOPMENT, AND NOTES THE INFLUENCEOF FOREIGN LIBRARY TRADITIONS. CONCLUDES THAT IN LIBRARY EDUCATION, AS IN MANYOTHER RESPECTS, ISRAEL IS A LABORATORY WHERE THE INTERPLAY OF DIFFERENT (ANDOFTEN CONTRADICTORY) SOCIAL FORCES AND DIVERSE CULTURAL TRADITIONS CAN BEOBSERVED AND, TO SOME EXTENT, TESTED